race.comment: ALBERTA BOUND (6) wasn't far away on debut last start over 1000m at Townsville, finishing second and beaten 2.5 lengths. Has ability and looks sure to measure up. SECRET SCOUT (1) has switched yards since finishing fifth three weeks ago over 1200m at Gold Coast Poly. Should be thereabouts. LIGHT MY LIFE (4) is a three-year-old filly by Set Alight out of Uppish stepping out on debut for the Trevor & Peter Rowe stable. Looks forward enough following a Cairns trial win. Worth watching for any market push. GOLDEN GLAZE (3) was a long way off them at Townsville on debut but gets onto his home deck today and will be better for that run.
